pace: 0pt;">
<table class=3D"body-component" width=3D"100%" border=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"=
0" cellpadding=3D"0">
<tr>
<td class=3D"body-component__content" style=3D"border-collapse: collapse; m=
so-table-lspace: 0pt; mso-table-rspace: 0pt; line-height: 150%; padding: 0 =
10px;">
<table class=3D"header" width=3D"100%" border=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" cellp=
adding=3D"0">
<tr>
<td class=3D"body-header-container" style=3D"border-collapse: collapse; mso=
-table-lspace: 0pt; mso-table-rspace: 0pt;">
<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">Sculptor</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I think there is a possible=C2=A0endgame now f=
or the Sculptor Capital Management Inc. situation?<a class=3D"footnote-inde=
x" href=3D"#footnote-1" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !imp=
ortant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bott=
om-style: none !important; background-color: transparent !important; displa=
y: inline-block;">
<span>[1]</span>
</a>=C2=A0It goes like this:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Right now, Sculptor has a deal to sel=
l itself to Rithm Capital Corp. for $11.15 per share. And it has a competin=
g bid from a group of hedge fund managers led by Boaz Weinstein, who want t=
o buy Sculptor for something like $13 per share. Sculptor=E2=80=99s board o=
f directors=C2=A0has, so far, refused to chuck the Rithm deal for Weinstein=
. Presumably the board hoped that Rithm would raise its price to something =
closer to $13.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">But after thinking =
about it for a bit, Rithm <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.co=
m/click/32995076.257419/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGV=
zLzIwMjMtMTAtMDYvcml0aG0tc2NyYXBzLWhpZ2hlci1zY3VscHRvci1iaWQtYWZ0ZXItbG9zaW=
5nLW9jaC1zLXN1cHBvcnQ_Y21waWQ9QkJEMTAxMTIzX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lb=
WFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjMxMDExJnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1t=
b25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB491ce8db" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" item=
scope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decorat=
ion: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #00000=
0; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> declined to raise =
its price</a>.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Sculptor could stil=
l ask its shareholders to vote to approve the Rithm deal. Last Thursday, it=
 filed another draft <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/cli=
ck/32995076.257419/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9BcmNoaXZlcy9lZGdhci9kYXRhLzE0=
MDMyNTYvMDAwMTE0MDM2MTIzMDQ3MTkwL255MjAwMDk5Mzl4MTFfcHJlcjE0YS5odG0/607f07c=
eef4b8524a319a23cB880ce20f" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" =
target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important=
; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-sty=
le: solid; background-color: #ccc;">proxy statement</a> for that vote, reco=
mmending that shareholders vote for the $11.15 Rithm deal.</li>=09<li style=
=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Will they,=C2=A0though? Sculptor=E2=80=99s stock c=
losed yesterday at $11.97. If you think that $11.15 is a good price, you sh=
ould sell your stock, today, to someone who doesn=E2=80=99t. Anyone who own=
s the stock by the time of the shareholder vote is going to want more than =
$11.15.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-2" style=3D"color: #00=
0000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bo=
ttom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; background-color=
: transparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[2]</span>
</a>=C2=A0</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Meanwhile, Weinstein ca=
n=E2=80=99t do anything to=C2=A0<em>force</em> Sculptor=E2=80=99s board to =
deal with him. In particular, as part of Sculptor=E2=80=99s original effort=
s to auction itself last year, Weinstein signed a nondisclosure agreement w=
ith a standstill clause barring him from making public offers to buy Sculpt=
or. Traditionally the way to bypass the board is with a tender offer: You j=
ust go out and offer to buy everyone=E2=80=99s shares for cash, and if more=
 than half of the shareholders tender=C2=A0then you control the company.<a =
class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-3" style=3D"color: #000000; text=
-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color=
: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; background-color: transpar=
ent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[3]</span>
</a>=C2=A0But Weinstein can=E2=80=99t do that, because of his NDA.</li>=09<=
li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">But Weinstein=E2=80=99s=C2=A0standstill ex=
pires on Dec. 22. It seems unlikely that Sculptor will be able to push thro=
ugh the Rithm deal before that. (There is no date set yet for the sharehold=
er vote.)=C2=A0Which means that Weinstein might be able to launch a tender =
offer and buy the company.</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">This is not an=C2=A0<em>optimal=C2=A0</em>endg=
ame. Weinstein would much rather come to a negotiated deal with Sculptor be=
fore December. For one thing, it would be faster. For another thing, tender=
ing blindly to buy Sculptor without reaching any agreement with the board o=
r management is=C2=A0<em>risky</em>. Weinstein is trying to buy=C2=A0an ass=
et manager with some $30 billion or so of assets under management, much of =
it not very locked up, and that=E2=80=99s a better deal if the clients plan=
 to stick around. If he can talk to Sculptor=E2=80=99s management, meet wit=
h the biggest clients, hear their concerns and reassure them, that reduces =
the risk that he=E2=80=99ll end up buying Sculptor and getting nothing.<a c=
lass=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-4" style=3D"color: #000000; text-=
decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color:=
 #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; background-color: transpare=
nt !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[4]</span>
</a> There are regulatory and business risks to buying an asset manager wit=
h a tender offer, and it would not be anyone=E2=80=99s first choice.<a clas=
s=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-5" style=3D"color: #000000; text-dec=
oration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #0=
00000; border-bottom-style: none !important; background-color: transparent =
!important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[5]</span>
</a></p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But Weinstein <em>probably</em>=C2=A0has the a=
bility to force that endgame, which means that he is in a better negotiatin=
g position to get the deal he wants. He can go to Sculptor and say:</p>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: disc; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;">=
=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Talk to me now, let me meet with your =
biggest clients and reassure them, and if all goes well we can sign a merge=
r agreement at $13 per share in cash.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5p=
x;">If you don=E2=80=99t, you=E2=80=99re still not going to get the Rithm d=
eal =E2=80=94=C2=A0shareholders will vote no =E2=80=94=C2=A0and I=E2=80=99l=
l do a tender offer in December. But it won=E2=80=99t be for $13. The delay=
 and annoyance will cost=C2=A0<em>your shareholders=C2=A0</em>something, be=
cause I=E2=80=99ll only pay $12.25 in the tender. I=E2=80=99ll still get th=
e company =E2=80=94=C2=A0$12.25 is more than $11.15, and more than it=E2=80=
=99ll be worth with no deal =E2=80=94=C2=A0but I=E2=80=99ll pay less than I=
 would if you negotiate now.</li>
</ul>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">So that=E2=80=99s what he did. Last Thursday=
=E2=80=99s <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/3299507=
6.257419/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9BcmNoaXZlcy9lZGdhci9kYXRhLzE0MDMyNTYvMD=
AwMTE0MDM2MTIzMDQ3MTkwL255MjAwMDk5Mzl4MTFfcHJlcjE0YS5odG0jdEJN/607f07ceef4b=
8524a319a23cBae7dd713" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" targe=
t=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; bor=
der-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: s=
olid; background-color: #ccc;"> proxy statement</a> lays out Weinstein=E2=
=80=99s ask: He offered to sign an agreement to buy Sculptor for $12.76 per=
 share, conditional on 40% of its hedge-fund clients consenting to the chan=
ge in management, but he also offered some sweeteners. For one thing, if Sc=
ulptor lets him talk to its estranged founder, Dan Och, and the other forme=
r executive managing directors who still own a big chunk of Sculptor, he mi=
ght raise his bid:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The September 30 Proposal reiterat=
ed the Consortium=E2=80=99s request to contact the Former EMD Group and ind=
icated that, depending on the outcome of its discussions and the Former EMD=
 Group=E2=80=99s willingness to enter into a rollover, the Consortium would=
 consider increasing its price to $13.00 per share of Class A Common Stock.=
=C2=A0</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">For another thing, if Sculptor lets him talk t=
o its=C2=A0<em>clients</em>, he might lower the client consent condition:</=
p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The Consortium noted that it may h=
ave the ability to further lower or eliminate the 40% client run-rate conse=
nt threshold for the Company=E2=80=99s Multi-Strategy and Opportunistic Cre=
dit business lines if it were permitted to speak with certain of the Compan=
y=E2=80=99s clients that comprise a substantial portion of the revenue asso=
ciated with those strategies.</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">So if Sculptor negotiates with Weinstein and a=
ll goes well, it could get a deal at $13 per share without much conditional=
ity. (Of course, all might not go well: If Sculptor=E2=80=99s board is real=
ly convinced that all of its big clients will say no to Weinstein, letting =
him talk to them will not get him to pay $13. It would get him to go away, =
though! Which also has some value.)</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But the proxy also lays out Weinstein=E2=80=99=
s threat about what will happen if the board doesn=E2=80=99t negotiate:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The Consortium further stated an i=
ntention to initiate a cash tender offer for a reduced price of $12.25 per =
share of Class A Common Stock following the expiration of Bidder J=E2=80=99=
s standstill on December 22, 2023, if the Company Stockholders had not appr=
oved the Merger Proposal prior to such time.</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">It=E2=80=99s a good threat: $12.25 is less tha=
n $13 (or $12.76), but more than $11.15. If you are a Sculptor shareholder,=
 asked to approve the $11.15 Rithm deal, you will be tempted to say no and =
hold out for the $12.25 Weinstein tender.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=
=3D"#footnote-6" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important;=
 border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-styl=
e: none !important; background-color: transparent !important; display: inli=
ne-block;">
<span>[6]</span>
</a>=C2=A0Which means there=E2=80=99s a good chance that the Rithm deal wil=
l fail and Weinstein will end up buying the company at $12.25. Which means =
that, for the board, it would be better to get $13 from Weinstein now than =
$12.25 from him later.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Meanwhile the board=C2=A0<em>was=C2=A0</em>wor=
king on a process in which:</p>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: disc; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;">=
=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Rithm would raise its price, maybe not=
 to $12.76 but to something closer than $11.15,<a class=3D"footnote-index" =
href=3D"#footnote-7" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !import=
ant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-=
style: none !important; background-color: transparent !important; display: =
inline-block;">
<span>[7]</span>
</a>=C2=A0and</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">in exchange, Och and=
 the other former executives would agree to support the Rithm deal, further=
 freezing out Weinstein.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-8" st=
yle=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-widt=
h: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important;=
 background-color: transparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[8]</span>
</a>
</li>
</ul>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">That would have been a good outcome for the bo=
ard: They get the deal they are comfortable with, and that they think clien=
ts will be comfortable with, but at a price that is good enough=C2=A0for sh=
areholders. But that didn=E2=80=99t work out, mostly because Weinstein rais=
ed his bid and Och decided Weinstein was better than Rithm, so Rithm =E2=80=
=9Cwas not prepared to (1) enter into the amended Merger Agreement without =
the Former EMD Support or (2) offer any other improvements to the terms and=
 conditions of the Merger Agreement or the Transactions.=E2=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And so Sculptor=E2=80=99s board, which has bee=
n pretty tough about ignoring Weinstein so far, has opened the door a crack=
. It=E2=80=99s writing a merger agreement to send to Weinstein:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">So as not to lose time while the S=
pecial Committee was evaluating whether to make a Superior=C2=A0Proposal De=
termination, the Special Committee authorized Latham &amp; Watkins to reque=
st Rithm=E2=80=99s consent to engage with the Consortium and instructed Lat=
ham &amp; Watkins to begin preparing revised draft definitive transaction d=
ocuments to send to the Consortium that the Special Committee would be prep=
ared to authorize at a price of $13.00 per share of Class A Common Stock.</=
p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And it=E2=80=99s not saying no:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The Special Committee determined to continue t=
o evaluate the September 30 Proposal with its advisors and continue to enga=
ge with Rithm regarding potential improvements to the terms and conditions =
of the Merger Agreement and the Transactions in parallel.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The Special Committee is continuing to evaluat=
e the September 30 Proposal, as amended by the October 2 Letter, in consult=
ation with its independent financial and legal advisors and will make its r=
ecommendation to the Company=E2=80=99s Board of Directors and determine nex=
t steps in due course. Consistent with its fiduciary duties, the Special Co=
mmittee and the Company=E2=80=99s Board of Directors will determine the bes=
t path forward with the interest of maximizing value for all Company Stockh=
olders.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">It seems like Weinstein has worn the board dow=
n enough that he might get his deal. Or, of course, <a href=3D"https://link=
.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/32995076.257419/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZ=
XJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMTAtMDMvdGhlLXNlYy1oYWQtYS1idXN5LXdl=
ZWs_Y21waWQ9QkJEMTAxMTIzX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmN=
lPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjMxMDExJnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f0=
7ceef4b8524a319a23cBaf9f2a30" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope=
" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !importa=
nt; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-s=
tyle: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> the board has worn Weinstein down en=
ough</a> that they might get $13 per share. Arguably this is a win for both=
 of them.</p>
