<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><em>Outside</em> of banking, meanwhile, Theory=
 1 is basically correct? That=E2=80=99s why people were so puzzled by SVB=
=E2=80=99s failure: Everywhere else in capital markets, it is just obvious =
that if you borrow short-term to buy long-duration assets, and rates go up,=
 you will lose money. Banks are special because their borrowing is technica=
lly short-term but really something else. But lots of other businesses are =
in this sort of maturity transformation business <em>without</em> that spec=
ial advantage. The Wall Street Journal <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombe=
rgbusiness.com/click/32995076.257419/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cud3NqLmNvbS9maW5hbmNlL2=
