<div id=3D"footnote-7" class=3D"footnote-content" style=3D"font-style: ital=
ic;">
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">[7] As part of raising its price, Rithm also w=
anted a higher termination fee. This is reasonable, and the board was okay =
with it, but it is a bit odd. The board was willing to give Rithm a higher =
termination fee, to protect its deal from being jumped by Weinstein, in exc=
hange for Rithm raising its price to *a price lower than Weinstein=E2=80=99=
s*. If Rithm had raised to $13.10, sure, give it a fully locked-up deal. Bu=
t raising to $12.20, when there=E2=80=99s a competing bid at $12.76 or so, =
does not really justify a higher breakup fee. Anyway they never signed it s=
o this is moot.</p>
</div>
<div id=3D"footnote-8" class=3D"footnote-content" style=3D"font-style: ital=
ic;">
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">[8] One other factor here is that Rithm=E2=80=
=99s deal still has a condition that 85% of clients have to consent. Given =
that the board keeps saying the Weinstein deal is too risky because it requ=
ires 80% of real-estate and collateralized-loan-obligation clients to conse=
nt, and 40% of hedge-fund clients, it is awkward that its preferred deal wi=
th Rithm requires 85%. The board can say that it is confident clients would=
 consent to Rithm and not Weinstein, but it=E2=80=99s odd to have a double =
standard in the formal document. It was trying to fix that in the revised R=
ithm deal: =E2=80=9CFollowing a discussion, the Special Committee determine=
d that it would ask Rithm to eliminate the Rithm Client Consent Condition i=
n the Merger Agreement. =E2=80=A6 On September 23, 2023, representatives of=
 Citi informed representatives of J.P. Morgan that assuming the Special Com=
mittee was otherwise prepared to agree to the other Proposed Amendments (an=
d subject to receiving the Former EMD Support), Rithm would agree to remove=
 the Rithm Client Consent Condition in the Merger Agreement.=E2=80=9D But t=
hen they never signed the amendment.</p>
</div>
<div id=3D"footnote-9" class=3D"footnote-content" style=3D"font-style: ital=
ic;">
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">[9] And =E2=80=A6  Credit Suisse Group AG? Ind=
irectly?</p>
</div>
<div id=3D"footnote-10" class=3D"footnote-content" style=3D"font-style: ita=
lic;">
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">[10] There is, however, a table of the co-auth=
ors=E2=80=99 individual results, which range from 48.7% to an  astounding 6=
0.1% (1,682 of 2,800, a 95% confidence interval of 58.2% to 61.9%) of flips=
 landing on the same side. Tianqi Peng of the University of Amsterdam could=
 make a killing flipping coins at Jane Street.</p>
</div>
</td>
